Gtk2::SourceView2
=================

Perl bindings for the C library "libgtksourceview2" that extends the standard
GTK+  framework for multiline text editing  with support for configurable syntax
highlighting, unlimited undo/redo, UTF-8 compliant caseless searching, printing
and other features typical of a source code editor.

For more information about libgtksourceview2 refer to the library's web site:

	http://projects.gnome.org/gtksourceview/


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

	perldoc Gtk2::SourceView2

Also feel free to take a look at the examples in the folder "examples/" and to
play around with them.

For any kind of help or support, simply send a mail to the gtk-perl mailing list
(gtk-perl-list@gnome.org) or join us in the IRC channel #gtk-perl on
irc.gnome.org.


